  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International frameworks\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Egmont Group of Financial Intelligence Units\n\n2. National-level legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (US)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Report (SAR) requirements\n\n3. Key enforcement mechanisms\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Customer due diligence\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Asset seizure and criminal prosecution\n\n4. Compliance requirements\n- Financial institutions must implement anti-money laundering programs\n- Regular reporting to financial intelligence units\n- Mandatory customer verification procedures\n\n5. International cooperation\n- Cross-border information sharing\n- Coordinated investigations\n- Extradition agreements\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
